  body
    h1 TimeStamp Microservice
    h2 This applicaton meets the following user stories
    ul
      li User Story: I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix 
      | timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016).

      li User Story: If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.

      li User Story: If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
      | footer

    h2 Example of use
    p: span.highlight=`${siteUrl}December 14, 2017`
    p: span.highlight=`${siteUrl}1670126400`

    h2 It should response: 
    p: span.highlight=example
